</para>
<para id="element-32">
<definition id="definition-32">
<term> Acceleration </term>
<meaning id="idp2371456"> Acceleration of a point body is equal to the second derivative of position vector with respect to time.
</meaning>
</definition>
</para>
<para id="element-32a">Now, position vector is represented in terms of  <link document="m14519" target-id="section-4b">components</link> as :
</para>

<para id="element-33">
<m:math display="block"> 
